This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it discusses the multi-access edge computing (MEC) paradigm, which involves processing content within the cellular network. It may also belong to the sub-category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as MEC networks may have security implications. Additionally, it could be classified under Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as MEC involves distributed computing within the cellular network. It may also fall under the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Multimedia (cs.MM) as MEC networks involve controlling and optimizing the processing of multimedia content.
